\begin_inset Formula $0.5$
\end_inset

.
 The spread in this range depends on the quantities of resources (time,
 energy, money, etc.) that are devoted to the experiment.
 In the classical setting, this 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

fuzziness
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 can be formalized by moving to 
\emph on
interval-valued probability measures
\emph default
 (IVPMs), which we explore in the next section, along with our proposed
 extension to the quantum domain.
